      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/01493708300940204826" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Molly</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2011/01/and-try-to-be-cheerful/#comment-25530"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2011-01-19T18:51:34-05:00">Wednesday, January 19, 2011 at 6:51 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Aimee, I&#39;m sorry for not getting back to you yesterday!  (Tuesday is my Sunday, and I try to stay away from the computer.)  The weight measurement for the ginger is mostly to help you when you&#39;re at the grocery store.  It&#39;s just a rough indication of how much ginger you need.  The 1/4 cup measurement is what you want to pay attention to when you actually make the recipe.  I hope that helps.</p>
    </div>

