    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>i visited this post so many times, thinking about the muffins and imagining them. my friends and i decided to do alternate breakfast days, where you bring something to one of our three early morning lectures. i am first. and so i made these. i had only one tablespoon of lemon, 100g salted butter, and no buttermilk, so i made some with a tablespoon of lemon juice and two blobs of natural yoghurt in my cup of milk. they are incredible. they are moist and perfumed with ginger and the slightest hint of lemon and they have this really delish outside, faintly chewy but with a delicate crunch. its late so i&#39;ve only had one with a glass of milk. but i see what you mean by wanting more.!!</p>
