      <p>I&#39;ll tell you why you keep the skin on the ginger, and why you get that nice domed shape. the skin of ginger actually contains natural yeast, so when you make the ginger-sugar syrup, you are actually starting a fermentation process. great, right????<br />this is also the basic recipe for making ginger beer, fyi.</p>
